		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_922649">Funny story, semi-applicable to this topic.  Once upon a time I had an engineer working in my organization that was god-awful horrible.  This was during the dot-com and fiber optic booms and we were having a hard time keeping engineers and would try to counter-offer people who were resigning.  <br />
<br />
Even in these circumstances this guy sucked so bad that I was in the middle of writing up a performance improvement plan, preparatory to shit canning him when lo and behold he came in with a resignation letter.  I snatched it from his hand so fast that the resultant friction must have come close to causing the letter to spontaneously combust.  He then stood there for a few minutes before asking if I was going to make a counter offer to keep him.  I politely explained that no, I had to much respect for him to attempt to entice him away from a decision that must have been painful for him to make.  After a few more minutes of silence he then explained that he didn't really want to resign, he was just trying to entice a counter offer pay raise out of me.  I had to regretfully inform him that since I had accepted his resignation already there was really nothing to be done and it was time to go clean out his desk.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
