<br />
That's EVIL. . . .  and nicely done.  <br />
<br />
We had a guy on a contract I was also working, got told APRIL 1 that his job would be elimintated OCTOBER 1.  He makes no effort to look for a job, and takes two + months off in the summer to go be a missionary somewhere in Africa.<br />
<br />
He comes back in September, and asks what we were going to have him doing after October 1st.<br />
<br />
Boss tells him, we have no idea, as you won't be employed by us at that point.<br />
<br />
He boggles.  <br />
<br />
We ended up taking up a collection and giving him a &quot;Severance Package and Job Training Program&quot;.  IT consisted of 3 1-dollar scratch-off lottery tickets, and a index card with the phrase &quot;Do you want fries with that ??&quot; on it. . . .<br />
<br />
I will admit that the &quot;training card&quot; was my idea, as was the faked request for an interview at the local strip club, the Crystal City Restaurant, which HE thought was &quot;CCR Associates&quot;. . . .</div>
