				&nbsp;<br />
				
				
				
				&nbsp;<br />
				<div>   </div>
			</div>				
	
	
	
	</td>
	
	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_922948">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_922948">Never take the counter-offer.<br />
<br />
What Wandor says is true.  Even if the company isn't actively looking to replace you, they will have identified you as the squeaky wheel, and will treat you as such.<br />
<br />
Should you find yourself in that situation, try to keep in mind why you're looking for a new job in the first place.  It's almost never <i>just</i> because of the money.  Frankly, your old employer is offering you <i>more</i> money, because they admit that they were underpaying you <i>and</i> that they're probably a worse place to work.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
