		<div id="post_message_922966"><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				Whatever you do, do not make either employer feel like you are only using them.
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
It's important for employers to know that.  It's the only incentive they have to reward excellence and provide retention thru their own excellence, rather than from outdated notions of loyalty which they themselves don't hold to.<br />
<br />
You guys that consider it a sign of disloyalty and that your employer will see you as someone that they should be replacing have bought the &quot;old labour&quot; line.  An employer in this economy should know that excellence will gravitate to excellent work and only where they are challenged and rewarded will they stay and thrive.  It's an important wake up call for a company that a lot of them aren't understanding after holding all the cards for so long.  Remember that your ambitious stars today are your potential rivals tomorrow.<br />
<br />
Of course, all of this is irrelevant if you sucked and they wanted rid of you all along.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
