	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_922990">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_922990">I think my experience might be unique to government contractors. A few years ago somebody sent me a job posting for a position that would deal with some tech they knew I'd be interested in. So I applied. After a few weeks the job offer came. I was very blatant with these folks that I loved my job, but that with the proper pile of money I'd consider leaving it, but I would not tell them how much I was currently making. They would have to divine the size of the pile required themselves. They come up with a pile of sufficient size. So I put in my resignation. I told the current boss I was absolutely not leaving for any reason other than cash. I had in the past had the &quot;why do you work?&quot; &quot;because you pay me.&quot; talk with this boss. I did tell him the job offer was around 40% increase in pay. He was told be the government to keep me. He did and I stayed.<br />
<br />
I think that in private industry one is unlikely to find an employer who'd play it the same way.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
